claims:
39. A glyphosate tolerant plant comprising:
a genome edited in a site-specific manner to modify EPSPS gene regulation, wherein said site-specific editing comprises operably linking an EPSPS gene to an alternative promoter at a native genomic location of the alternative promoter, operably linking an EPSPS gene to a recombinant promoter at a native genomic location of the EPSPS gene, or introducing an enhancer into an endogenous EPSPS regulatory sequence;
wherein said modification to EPSPS gene regulation is effective to cause an altered expression profile of an EPSPS gene compared to an EPSPS gene expression profile of a non-edited plant genome;
wherein said altered expression profile of said EPSPS gene confers glyphosate tolerance.
